06/10/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Ambassador-at-large for War Crimes Issues Pierre-Richard Prosper and the BiH presidency plan to discuss court investigations Monday (6 October) in Sarajevo.
Slobodan Radulj, a legal adviser to presidency member Borislav Paravac, told the local press that war crimes trials at The Hague would be the focus of the meeting.
Radulj said the UN tribunal should investigate all war crimes in the former Yugoslavia, regardless of the ethnic groups involved.
(SRNA, BBC, BHTV1, HINA - 05/10/03)
